  "description": "A duck floating on a small pond. The bill was blue gray with a large blackish nail. Just behind the nail was a lighter, whitish area. The head had, in some light, a purplish sheen. The breast was dark brown but mottled with white and lighter than the face. The back feathers were dark brown but some, the tertials had a glossy bluish sheen. The flanks where brown with with whitish edges to most of the feathers giving the bird a mottle look. The individual flank feathers appeared worn in my photos. The bird had a long whitish wing stripe (see photos) that included both the secondaries and the primaries. It had whitish undertail coverts. The prominent feature was a dark tuft at the rear crown of the bird, separating it from all other duck species except hybrids.Behaviors: Dove, swam slowly, preened, a extended its wings on occasion.Call: silentPlumage: 1st winter",
